name: Teamsters endorsement
summary: The International Brotherhood of Teamsters, a powerful labor union in the United States, has announced that it will not endorse any candidate in the upcoming 2024 presidential election. This decision was made after internal polling revealed that the majority of Teamsters members support former President Donald Trump. As a result, California Governor and Democratic candidate Kamala Harris's high-stakes endorsement interview with the union did not result in an endorsement. Despite speculation that Trump might receive the Teamsters' endorsement, the union ultimately declined to endorse either candidate, dealing a blow to Democrats who had hoped to secure the support of a major labor organization.

name: Adrian Wojnarowski
summary: Adrian Wojnarowski, a prominent NBA insider, has retired from his position at ESPN to assume the role of general manager for his alma mater, St. Bonaventure University's basketball program. This decision marks a significant shift for Wojnarowski, who had become synonymous with sports journalism and breaking news in the NBA. The announcement has been met with both surprise and admiration, as Wojnarowski's departure from ESPN leaves a void in the industry. His return to St. Bonaventure represents a full circle moment, fulfilling a dream he had as a student there. Wojnarowski's expertise and connections will undoubtedly be valuable assets to the Bonnies basketball program, as he transitions into this new chapter in his career.

summary: Hayden Panettiere has given her first interview since the sudden death of her brother, Jansen Panettiere. In the interview, she opens up about her grief and the impact it has had on her life. She reveals that she has been struggling with agoraphobia and has experienced rapid weight gain. Panettiere also discusses the "horrific" paparazzi photos that were taken after her brother's death, which she says contributed to her struggles. Many celebrities and fans have expressed concern over Panettiere's appearance and demeanor in the interview, with some calling it "uncomfortable" and "sad." Her representative has since spoken out, saying that Panettiere is grieving and should be given space.

name: Carly Gregg
summary: A trial is underway in Mississippi for Carly Gregg, a 14-year-old girl accused of shooting and killing her mother. Chilling video footage from the kitchen camera shows Gregg casually using her phone shortly after gunshots and screams were heard from her mother's bedroom. A psychiatrist testified that Gregg has no memory of the shooting. In a 911 call released at the trial, someone can be heard exclaiming, "She killed her mom!" Gregg's stepfather and other witnesses have provided testimony in the case. Gregg's defense team has rested its case, and the court has heard from a body camera video of police officers responding to the scene and testimony from a medical expert. State experts have testified that Gregg denied hearing voices before the killing.

name: JD Souther
summary: JD Souther, a renowned singer-songwriter known for his collaborations with the Eagles and Linda Ronstadt, has passed away at the age of 78. Souther's songwriting contributions to the Eagles' iconic tracks "New Kid in Town" and "Heartache Tonight" have left an indelible mark on the music industry. His musical abilities extended to writing hits for other artists as well, cementing his legacy in the world of country-rock music. Tributes have poured in from family, friends, and fans, honoring the influential songwriter and his timeless creations.
